Proposed Near-Term Extensions

1. Context inheritance

Allow expressions to inherit shared context from a block:

@context economic recession
@perspective worker perspective

policy_A ≈ policy_B ⟨economic recession, worker perspective, 0.62⟩
wage_freeze ≈ temporary_stability ⟨economic recession, worker perspective, 0.51⟩

2. Context variables

Allow symbolic context bindings:

C1 = "economic recession"
P1 = "worker perspective"

policy_A ≈ policy_B ⟨C1, P1, 0.62⟩

3. Comparator libraries

Domain-specific operator packs:
	•	semantic reasoning
	•	policy reasoning
	•	scientific model comparison
	•	legal interpretation
	•	AI output evaluation

⸻

Guardrails
	•	CPU notation is a conditioning formalism, not a license for vagueness.
	•	It should increase precision, not reduce accountability.
	•	It must preserve fact/inference separation.
	•	Context cannot be used to erase empirical contradiction.
	•	Perspective cannot be used as a shield for unsupported claims.

⸻

Closing Statement

The equals sign made equivalence compact.

The CPU operator attempts to do the same for conditioned truth.

It does not replace mathematics.
It extends formal expression toward domains where:
	•	context matters
	•	perspective matters
	•	uncertainty matters

That is the direction of the proposal.

